# 🎬 Integrated Movie Recommendation System

> A Hybrid Movie Recommendation System built using **Content-Based Filtering**, **Collaborative Filtering (SVD)**, 
and a **Hybrid Recommendation Engine** using Rotten Tomatoes movie and review datasets.

---

## 📖 Project Overview

This project combines multiple recommendation techniques to provide accurate and 
personalized movie suggestions through a modern React-based user interface and a Python-powered backend.

### ✨ Key Highlights

✅ Content-Based Filtering using TF-IDF & Cosine Similarity

✅ Collaborative Filtering using SVD (Surprise Library)

✅ Hybrid Recommendation Model

✅ Advanced Movie Filtering & Sorting

✅ React + Tailwind CSS Frontend

✅ Python Backend API

---

## 🔍 Search Capabilities

Users can search movies by:

🎬 Movie Title

🎭 Genre

🎥 Director

---

## 🎛️ Available Filters

Users can refine recommendations using:

⭐ Rating

🌐 Language

🎥 Director

📅 Release Year Range

---

# 🚀 Features

## 🎯 Content-Based Recommendation

Uses movie metadata:

* 🎭 Genre
* 🎥 Director
* ⭐ Rating
* 🌐 Original Language

### Technique Used

* TF-IDF Vectorization
* Linear Kernel Similarity

---

## 🤝 Collaborative Filtering

Uses critic reviews from Rotten Tomatoes.

### Implemented Using

* Surprise Library
* Singular Value Decomposition (SVD)

---

## 🧠 Hybrid Recommendation Engine

Combines both recommendation approaches:

Hybrid Score =

0.6 × Content Score

*

0.4 × Collaborative Score

### Benefits

✅ Better Accuracy

✅ Better Personalization

✅ Reduced Cold Start Impact

---

## 🎛️ Advanced Filtering

Filter movies by:

* ⭐ Rating
* 🌐 Language
* 🎥 Director
* 📅 Release Year

---

## 📊 Sorting Options

Sort recommendations using:

📈 Hybrid Score

🍿 Audience Score

🍅 Tomato Meter

💬 Critic Sentiment (Quality Score)

📅 Release Year

---

